I’m at the edit step now. I’m making the verifier conservative around the `safeApprove` edge case in `tokenAllowAll`: it will follow the required path exactly when allowance is `0` or already `type(uint256).max`, and it will avoid silently switching to a different route if the on-chain allowance state makes that stage impossible.
